data.title: Mark Owen to join Robbie Williams at Sandringham concerts
data.meta_description: Take That star Mark Owen is among the special guests joining Robbie Williams at his Sandringham concerts in summer 2023.
data.text:
Robbie Williams is performing two sold-out concerts at the Royal Estate in Norfolk over the weekend of August 26 and 27 2023.

His special guests will be former bandmate Mark Owen, who performs both nights, with chart-topping singer-songwriters Dagny opening Saturday and Lucy Spraggan opening Sunday.

Following his celebrated slot at the Isle of Wight Festival in June, these will be Williams' only outdoor shows in the UK this year.

READ MORE: 7 major Norfolk events to look forward to in July

It was also the first large-scale live music event to be announced at Sandringham.

Mark Owen is best known as a member of Take That and he has also forged a successful solo career releasing five albums, including Land of Dreams which was released in September 2022.

READ MORE: Rumoured setlist for N-Dubz's summer concert in Norwich park

Since her breakthrough in 2016, Dagny Norvoll Sandvik has established herself as one of Norwayâ€™s biggest artists.

Lucy Spraggan shot to fame on ITV's The X Factor more than a decade ago and her latest album Balance will be released in August 2023.

Also performing at the Sandringham Estate this summer, with the concert series organised by Heritage Live, is Van Morrison on August 25 and The Who on August 28.
